<br>
I'm not taking tanking into consideration.  The Air pet tanks head over heels better than the water.  These are just some observations/questions that I need verified.<br>
<br>
1)  Air pet can hold agro through insane amounts of nuking *ONLY* if it chain stuns right off the bat.  I'm assuming this is just like a Paladin, but let me explain.  I trio with a warrior and shaman (who are actually two boxed by the same person) at the PoI entrance.  Malosi does not create much agro, suprisingly enough, so if another group is fighting alongside us, my pulls often add to them and not me, like they're supposed to.  In order to grab the mob off the other group, I cast Char on it to ensure those buggers come straight at me.  During this pull, I had gotten hit at least once, so when the mob added to the other group, my pet decided to start chomping on its rear end.  I never expected my air pet to hold agro from me nuking, but somehow, it did.  So I nuked again.  Low and behold, the mob is still not moving.  The 53 air pet had just held agro through slightly over 1600 points of damage from my nuking.  Now, I'm watching this whole deal.  The mob is chewing on the backside of a bard and no one else is touching it except my pet.  We ended up having to kill the mob where it was standing.  If the warrior began smacking on the mob and attempting to position, the mob would stay put and continue smacking on my pet.  <br>
<br>
2)  I keep my other hits on in a different window to give myself a good idea of who's doing what damage.  Usually in PoI, I either bring out my air or water pet depending on the situation.  For the first 2 seconds of the mobs existance, my pet tanks until the warrior steps into position.  Remember, I'm trioing here, but the warrior/shaman are being played by the same person, so it takes a second or two for him to respond since he's playing two characters at once.  When we get into position after a few seconds, I sit there and boot nuke with my Boots of Blade Calling, cast Sirocco, boot nuke again, and watch the mob fall over.  Meanwhile, I'm watching both the warrior and pet quad away.  Between using both my air and water pets, I noticed the Air pet seems to land and quad quite a bit more than the water pet does.  Is it possible that despite the Rogue status of the water pet, the Air could quite possibly have a higher innate attack?  Or could this be that the Air pet has a lower innate delay?  The water pet, in the end, still seems to do more damage, but only due to its backstab ability it seems.  <br>
<br>
Btw, both pets are buffed with BurnoutIII and given Muzzle of Mardu.  Despite having a shaman, we usually don't bother buffing the pet with Focus of Spirit or anything like that.  Mana is scarce and we never know when a train of 4 mobs are going to come barelling past us chasing a rogue who never had the courtesy to /shout &quot;Train!&quot;.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 601<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 3:43:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=971.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Observations of the Air Pets</span><hr size=1> My air pet (Ward of Xegony) OFTEN has insane aggro. When farming Seb i sometimes pull with Firebolt of Tallon (2k+, sometimes 4k+ if i crit), and good ol' Air can steal aggro on one stun.<br>
